news.title: Macrotech Developers sales booking up 51% to Rs 9,024 crore in FY22
news.para: Among listed entities, Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which markets its properties under Lodha brand, Godrej Properties, Bengaluru-based Prestige Estates and DLF are in the race to become the country's largest real estate developer in terms of sales bookings during the last financial year.

news.title: MahaRERA project data integration to prevent illegal property registrations
news.para: “This will be an inbuilt check. With this, registered projects’ MahaRERA number will automatically reflect in the survey number column to enable the citizens and officials to know if a project has been registered with the state real estate authority,” a senior MahaRERA official said on Wednesday.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents move SC say government has failed to protect interests
news.para: The petitioners told TOI they were exasperated by the delay in getting a structural audit of the condominium, where the hall areas of five flats in Tower D caved in on February 10, done by IIT-Delhi.
